  "prompt": "Which is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Hancock County IL?",
  "response": "There are several reputable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab centers near Hancock County, IL, that offer comprehensive treatment programs. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n### 1. **Rosecrance Treatment Centers**\n   - **Location:** Multiple locations in Illinois, including nearby Rockford and Champaign.\n   - **Services:** Rosecrance offers inpatient and outpatient programs for substance abuse and mental health disorders. They provide individualized treatment plans, including detox, therapy, and aftercare support.\n   - **Website:** [Rosecrance.org](https://www.rosecrance.org/)\n\n### 2. **Gateway Foundation**\n   - **Location:** Springfield, IL (approximately 2 hours from Hancock County).\n   - **Services:** Gateway Foundation offers inpatient and outpatient programs for substance abuse, including detox, counseling, and family therapy. They also provide specialized programs for co-occurring mental health disorders.\n   - **Website:** [GatewayFoundation.org](https://www.gatewayfoundation.org/)\n\n### 3. **Chestnut Health Systems**\n   - **Location:** Bloomington, IL (approximately 2.5 hours from Hancock County).\n   - **Services:** Chestnut Health Systems offers inpatient and outpatient treatment for substance use disorders. They provide evidence-based therapies, including cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT) and motivational interviewing.\n   - **Website:** [Chestnut.org](https://www.chestnut.org/)\n\n### 4. **The Farley Center**\n   - **Location:** Alton, IL (approximately 1.5 hours from Hancock County).\n   - **Services:** The Farley Center offers both inpatient and outpatient treatment programs. They focus on a holistic approach to recovery, including individual and group therapy, family involvement, and aftercare planning.\n   - **Website:** [Farleycenter.com](https://www.farleycenter.com/)\n\n### 5. **Caron Treatment Centers**\n   - **Location:** While the main facility is in Pennsylvania, Caron offers a \u201cCaron Illinois\u201d program with services available in the Midwest.\n   - **Services:** Caron provides inpatient and outpatient treatment, including detox, individual counseling, and family therapy. They are known for their comprehensive approach to addiction treatment.\n   - **Website:** [Caron.org](https://www.caron.org/)\n\n### Things to Consider:\n- **Insurance Coverage:** Verify if the rehab center accepts your insurance plan.\n- **Program Length:** Inpatient programs typically range from 28 days to several months, depending on the severity of the addiction.\n- **Specialized Services:** Consider whether you need specialized care (e.g., dual diagnosis, LGBTQ+ support, or trauma-informed care).\n\nIt\u2019s important to contact these facilities directly to learn more about their programs, availability, and whether they meet your specific needs. Additionally, consulting with a healthcare professional or addiction specialist can help guide you to the best option for recovery.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
